meta.description: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club (Gate B18) at Hartsfield–Jackson Atlanta International Airport (ATL), Concourse B. Learn more about the lounge: amenities, photos, review, opening hours, location.

lounge.name: Delta Air Lines Delta Sky Club (Gate B18)

location.terminalDirections: Above the Concourse Level, near Gate B18.

lounge.description: This 25,000 square foot flagship oasis is a modern, state-of-the-art retreat that allows for relaxation, productivity, or both. With acclaimed Atlanta Chef Linton Hopkins' locally inspired food selection, a gallery highlighting Atlanta artwork, and a wine wall curated by Master Sommelier Andrea Robinson, not to mention unbeatable views, this truly is the perfect escape from the most heavily trafficked concourses in global aviation history.

reviews.content: Spacious and lots of seating. Free booze. Food choices limited during covid. All prepackaged. Good views. Worth the detour.
Huge and open and therefore LOUD. The food was all packaged and there was nothing hot. Overheard staff at the food area cursing (f-word) which is fine but come on.
Nice and clean; service was good.
A single large, crowded, loud open space, unlike my preferred Sky Clubs that have a sizable open space but also provide smaller, quieter spaces out of the main traffic flow. Still beats gate life!
The lounge is spacious but it can remain fairly busy. Solid hot and cold meal selection which seem to be constantly replenished. Very friendly and attentive staff. Worth a stop if you have the time.
The heavy favorite for Delta Sky Club members, and b/c of that it can get crowded. Food is usually decent if they aren’t running out of it every 5 minutes. Great views of life on the runway.
With views of the east and west side of B concourse below. The lounge sits high above the airport offering an above average hot and cold buffet line. Unique and pleasing decor. And average drinks.
Flagship for a reason. Big and new. Very nice. Food is always replenished. Good bartenders.
Probably one of the better Sky Clubs on the Delta network. Friendly staff, lots of seating, well presented lounge. Great views of the ramp area at ATL.
I’ve been coming here regularly since it opened. I loved it but now there is a HUGE fruit fly problem. I’m constantly swatting them away. GROSS. Tells me the cleanliness is lacking. Please fix it!
WiFi regularly useless, food options less than other Delta clubs. If you have the time, the club in F is the way to go.
Pretty good for a domestic lounge. I would say this lounge is second only to the Centurion lounges.
This is my favorite lounge for domestic flights. Even if my flight leaves from another concourse, I’ll go to this one.
Pretty disappointing. Food is decent if you’re not lactose intolerant. Non-alcoholic drink options is very limited. Too crowded and lots of dirty tables...
Huge lounge. Yes, busy. But still relaxing even when busy. Definitely has an oasis atmosphere separate from the gates!
If you want to wait in line to get in and don't mind waiting again in line for a drink then go here.  Honestly, I'm a Diamond who makes over a mil a year and expect more.  This lounge seems for all.
Huge space! Optimum bar and food selections. At night, the place can be very cold.
The staff makes this lounge. They are always warm and welcoming. The lounge is nice and bright, but would be better if there were a quiet area with loungers.

Flying through in the afternoon. Food selection is pretty diverse - hot soup, pasta, crudités, cheese, and pretzels/popcorn. Comp wine, beer, and select spirits. Lots of seating and bright atmosphere.
The food is very good; chick salad, pimento, potato and pasta salads, soups, breads, Starbucks coffee, beer, wine, cocktails. working spaces with outlets, plenty of comfortable semi-private seats.
Better than most of the best lounges I have been to internationally. Great food selection, nice bar and attentive staff. It's worth paying for if you have a long layover.
Wow, completely surprised by the quality! If a Cathay or Virgin Atlantic lounge is a 10, this Sky Club is a solid 8. Very good food, ample seating, self serve fountain drinks. Great job by Delta.
A surprise from Delta, a terrible airline but this lounge is very nice. Needs a place to lay and sleep to begin to approach a Centurion Lounge but I was very pleased. Food was excellent, service too.
The nicest Delta lounge I've been to. It has the most expansive food selection of any Delta lounge I've been to. The staff were excellent. It was packed but I quickly found a seat, beer, and food.
Woman at the front desk dropped the ball a bit, they ran out of forks at the buffet and hit entrees were limited, but overall a great lounge. I will be back.
Possibly the best Delta lounge in the country.
Very new lounge in the center of B concourse with sweeping views from both sides. Food is delicious and the bar is expansive. Many comfortable places to sit with power outlets a plenty.
The flagship lounge. Huge bar. Good food selection. Very spacious. Probably as close as Delta gets to Centurion.
This lounge has great views out both sides of the B concourse. Very spacious and big. Huge self serve wine selection ($$$). Other alcohol is free. Best lounge in ATL.
New spacious lounge with great tarmac views. Food selection far better than other domestic lounges. Large bar plus self service wine offerings. Great staff.
Well worth the $59 single day pass. Lots of soups, salads and snacks to choose from. 12 seats at the bar with 4 large screens. Spacious bathroom stalls.
Great brand new lounge! Nicer now than the International lounges at ATL. Very open, lots of seating great bar area and wine tasting station. Best lounge in ATL.
